For the tomatoes, place the sliced tomatoes into a bowl and sprinkle over the curry powder and flour.Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and fry the tomatoes until lightly golden-brown on both sides. Remove the tomatoes from the pan and drain on kitchen paper while you make the raita.For the raita, mix the yoghurt with the chopped herbs in a small bowl.To serve, place the tomatoes onto a serving plate with the bowl of raita alongside.